Sep 25 2009 	Comfort and good value in a central location	We used the Donatello for three nights, on arrival from UK and whilst waiting to pick up an RV. I chose this hotel on the basis of comments by other guests on TripAdvisor and was not disappointed. The staff on Reception were very friendly and happy to give advice on getting the best out of our short stay. The bedroom was huge (as was the bathroom) and had a kitchenette of sink, microwave, fridge and coffee maker. The on-line rate seemed excellent value, as it included continental breakfast. this has recently been improved - it is now served on the mezzanine floor alongside the restaurant, so there is a better supply of fruit, cereal and savouries to supplement the pastries and coffee. The hotel is just one block from Union Square, which reduces the noise, and a short walk (even with wheeled cases) from the BART and the cable car terminus. A good location for sight-seeing, as you can go north to Fisherman's Wharf on the cable car and then come back via the trams along the coast.	
