Sep 18 2009 	wonderful stay	From the moment we arrived at the Donatello we were treated like honored guests by the parking attendant, bellman and front desk receptionist. Because it was our wedding anniversary, we were treated to a complimentary bottle of wine and chocolates. Our room was spacious and, as requested, on a higher floor off the street to escape the city noises. The funky furnishings were pleasant and very functional, with lots of storage space. The mini kitchen was very handy for snackers like us. The club room on the top floor was a lovely place to sit and talk. The continental breakfast in the restaurant was very adequate and like us, we saw that most people had vouchers and didn't have to pay the normal $7 charge. The only negatives were some peeling paint on the bottom of our bathroom door, discolored grout around the tub that didn't look clean even if it was, and a loose faucet in the mini bar. But I considered those minor for a great hotel at the right price in the heart of the action where you could walk everywhere. We even walked to the pier for the Alcatraz Ferry. Would I stay at the Donatello again? You Bet!	
