Aug 8 2009 	Best hotel I've been to in San Francisco.	I have been to numerous Hotels in San Francisco including some of the very pricey hotels located directly in Union Square, and this hotel was by far the nicest. It is really a great deal. The rooms are very modern,clean, and spacious. The bed was very comfortable. I slept very well. There is also a sofa bed that some members of our party slept on, and they said that was pretty comfortable as well. The windows are large, so the view is good. There is also a refrigerator, microwave, toaster, and coffee machine in the room. The front desk staff members are very friendly. It location is just a couple of blocks from Union Square. There is also a Walgreens nearby in case you need anything in a rush. I read reviews on this hotel before I booked it, and some complain about noise. Well, San Francisco is always noisy. It is a city so there is always something going on, and there are always sirens. There is a nightclub across the street from the hotel which does have a little bit of noise but it is not really noticeable or unbearable. I'd say that the room was pretty quiet compared to rooms I've stayed in elsewhere. The only negative is that the continental breakfast is $4.00 for 2 pastries and a fruit. However, one can't really complain when the rooms are so wonderful for such a great price. And they do offer free hot chocolate, coffee, and tea which is great. GREAT GREAT GREAT HOTEL! Our stay was very enjoyable.	
