Jul 3 2009 	Nice hotel and with friendly staff and comfortable rooms.	The Donatello for the most part met my expectations during my five night stay.After researching sites like Trip Advisor and finding an excellent rate at this hotel, I decided to give the Donatello a try. The rooms were quite large with ample space to spread out. The queen-sized bed was comfortable. I was fortunate enough to get a corner room and experienced minimal hallway traffic and noise. The room's layout and cleanliness were good but the quality of furniture and lighting seemed below average for this level of hotel class. Since I was on the fifth floor, there was also a fair amount of street noise. The bathroom was a pleasant surprise with a convenient layout, plenty of counter top space and clean towels. Overall feeling of cleanliness was extremely high similar to what one can find at a five or six star hotel.The continental breakfast was basic but good. Sliced bread, bagels, donuts and pastries and fresh fruit were available. Coffee was quite good and served hot. Every morning, the tiny breakfast room and outside deck areas were crowded with as many guests as it can hold. The fitness center is across from the breakfast room and small with one treadmill, cycling machine and some free weights.The Donatello is little more than one block away from Union Square and about five blocks from the trolley car station. During the day, the area around the hotel seems to be relatively safe. Many nights walking back to the hotel was uneventful with a decent amount of people and cars still going through the area. Most memorable was the friendliness of the hotel staff. They were very approachable and helpful and keen on making your stay a pleasant one. Overall the service was highly commendable with generously-sized and comfortable rooms. The hotel is unpretentious and well-kept. The Donatello can offer tremendous value when staying in San Francisco.	
