Feb 22 2009 	One Word: Awesome!!!	On the Presidents day weekend a few friends &amp; I headed to San Francisco for the weekend &amp; we elected to stay at the Donatello. Although the hotel is part of the Shell Vacations Club, anyone can stay there.The staff at the hotel were friendly, courteous, accommodating (E.G. Late Check Out), overall Awesome. The hotel was very clean &amp; well kept. Both our rooms were Hugh compared to some rooms I have stayed in San Francisco &amp; included a mini fridge, microwave, coffee maker, coffee, utensils, etc. The room had a pull out sofa which was larger than normal &amp; the king size bed was awesome. There is lots of storage space for your clothes, either in drawers or in a closet. The bathrooms were a good size which I think could accommodate someone in a wheelchair, but if you are someone who needs wheelchair access I would suggest you contact the hotel just to make sure. All rooms have flat screen TV's, CD &amp; DVD players. There are windows in the room that do open just enough so that a child can't fall out, which I like as I prefer fresh air over a ventilation system, however it did have both. With the windows open I did sometime notice the noise at night but I did have the option of closing the window plus you are in San Francisco what can one expect. The hotel provides a FREE, yes free, continental breakfast every morning, which included bagels, muffins, pastries, fresh fruit, coffee, tea, orange juice which was good enough to get you through the morning. On Friday afternoons they also provide a FREE, yes free, 2 hr wine &amp; cheese tasting on the Club floor which is at the top of the hotel where the continental breakfast is provided each morning &amp; where there is a small but adequate gym, co-ed whirlpool &amp; saunas in each of the change rooms, which also have showers. The Gym, whirlpool, sauna's &amp; change rooms were VERY well kept.The hotel is conveniently located about a 5 to 10 minute walk from the BART's Powell St station, which is San Franciscos light rail subway system that runs from San Francisco International Airport &amp; only costs a mere $5.35 US per person one way &amp; takes approximately 35 to 45 minutes to get from the airport to the Powell St station, which I highly recommend as its quick &amp; cheap plus I think the BART is the cleanest public transit system I've been on in years, in fact there were people walking through the train on our way to the hotel picking up garbage, talk about impressive. The overall location of the hotel was great, close to Union Square for those who like to shop, lots of restaurants, China town was a few blocks away &amp; access to the BART, MUNI, buses &amp; street cars were only a few minutes away. I took a street car (not a Cable car, they are $5.00 per person) from one of the many stations located on Market St ( which is which is about a 5 to 10 minute walk from the hotel) to Fisherman's Warf &amp; it was only $1.50 per person one way &amp; the transfer I was given was good for almost 3 hrs. At the hotel both the Concierge desk on the main floor or the one on the Club floor can make arrangements for all your travel needs (Tours, Restaurants, etc) &amp; at reasonable prices. One thing to keep in mind parking in San Francisco is not cheap, so if you can get by without renting a car try using there transit systems, its awesome. This hotel was great for me (a 46 yr old professional male) &amp; my friends, in short, if you want a clean, friendly, well located &amp; reasonably priced hotel, try The Donatello. I hope you enjoy your stay as much as we did. Cheers, ChristopherCalgary, Canada	
