Feb 17 2009 	Excellent Hotel - Would stay at no other hotel in San Francisco	It was my first stay in San Francisco. A colleague had recommended another nearby hotel in the city....but that other place did not have air conditioning nor a refrigerator in the room. Since I was staying in the city for two weeks, I definitely wanted both those things. So after reading the reviews here and at other sites, I decided on The Donatello. It was great! My room was huge! And while some other reviews recommended asking for a room away from the street to reduce the noise.....my room was on the 8th floor and facing the street and I only heard noise outside at night a few times (more so during the weekends than during the week.) The bed was extremely comfortable, the pillows were great (two things I'm very picky about!) Turn-down service each night with chocolates left at your bed side. I did not eat at the restaurant in the hotel because there were so many wonderful restaurants to choose from within one or two blocks from the hotel. Great location...near Union Square....about four blocks from the BART station at Powell street. There was only one thing that I had an issue with....and that was the wireless internet service. The signal in my room was too low to ever connect to my laptop. However I was able to use the hotel guest computer the few times that I needed it.....plus I used my computer all day long at my work location so not having a computer in my room was not a huge issue - although it would have been nice to have during the weekend when I was planning my stops at some of the tourist spots. I only went to the breakfast buffet on the weekend. Not much there other than pastries, bagels, juice and coffee.....but again, plenty of restaurants close by and if you're there on a Saturday morning, the best bet for breakfast is the Farmer's Market at Ferry Plaza. Not sure if my travels will take me back to San Francisco but if I do go back, I will stay at no other hotel!	
