Dec 9 2008 	Simple things done well.	Stayed at the Donatello for 8 nights in November 08 and have little or no complaints. A lick of paint is needed in a few places but otherwise this hotel is fine. Good staff and service and a prime location for downtown (although everywhere else can be reached by foot, taxi, MUNI or BART). But the real winner is the large rooms. These are a real bonus. If you hate hotels rooms where to seem to just bounce from wall to furniture to wall, then this is the place for you. Rooms had all the cons one wants and needs. The simple breakfast offered in the Club Floor is adequate and suited our tastes. The Club floor is small and not a formal dining area, so a lot of folks (I think) chose to eat elsewhere  there are plenty of Diners nearby. In all, the breakfast arrangement is very low-key, offers a gentle start to the day and is a breath of fresh air compared to the noisy dining halls at similar sized hotels. Finally, we did not hear one other British accent during our stay at this hotel  what joy!	
Dec 3 2008 	Great San Francisco experience	We recently stayed at the Donatello over Thanksgiving with some friends from Oregon. Contributing to our wonderful time in San Francisco were the comfortable accommodations we enjoyed at the Donatello. Our rooms (which were the same) were large, clean, and contained all of the amenities one would expect from this caliber of hotel including a refrigerator, microwave, coffee maker, and a small sink. The staff was very congenial and ready to meet our every request with eagerness. The morning continental breakfast consisting of many food choices was delightful and more than sufficient to prepare us for our day's excursion. We have stayed at the Donatello before so we felt comfortable inviting guests to join us this time, and they enjoyed their experience as much as we did. We look forward to returning in the near future.	
Dec 2 2008 	Wonderful rooms and beds at the Donatello	We have just completed a one week stay at the Donatello, and loved it. The rooms are large and clean, and the beds (king size) are superbly comfortable! The colour scheme is royal blue and orange - it sounds weird, but it really works. The bathrooms are good, and there is good storage space in the bathroom and the room in general. Rooms have a microwave, fridge, coffee maker, dishes and cutlery - tea, coffee and sugar are supplied.The staff, especially Jesus, couldn't have been more helpful and friendly.The only problem we had was noise from the nightclub on Mason St, but Jesus moved us to another room, and then all was well. Don't stay in a room overlooking Mason!The restaurant is wonderful, but not cheap.	
Dec 1 2008 	Great staff fantastic location	We stayed at the Donatello from Oct. 27 to Nov. 4 of this year; our second time at this hotel. LOCATION LOCATION LOCATION you cant get any better than this hotel! It is one short block to Union Square (5-minute walk), and is a perfect base for San Francisco, near all the sites and shopping places. It is also a safe place to be, and we had no worries walking around the area at night. A huge Borders is practically across the street (2-minute walk), and is open till very late. For meals, we enjoyed Sears (right beside Borders), which has the best pancakes in the city.Considering the hotel is right in the heart of the city, the room was very spacious, with a small kitchenette that had a fridge, microwave, coffeemaker. This was in addition to a king-sized and very comfortable bed and large sofa bed, TV and video player. A major factor for return guests is that the staff is exceptional: friendly, helpful, knowledgeable. Special mention must go to Mark San Felipe, whom you could always rely on to give you the best tips for places to go for meals and shopping. Whether early morning or very late at night, the front desk staff was unfailingly approachable, and this made our stay very pleasant indeed. In fact, Jet Blue lost my luggage on our first night there, and the hotel staff did all it could to help and assure me; looking up the necessary phone numbers, with Mark advising me on the best way to deal with the problem. His advice proved very useful, as I was able to pick up my luggage from the airport the next day, instead of relying on Jet Blue to deliver it to me at the hotel (and risk the luggage being misplaced again!)There is no other place Ill stay in when in San Francisco.	
