Nov 14 2008 	Spacious room but lots of street noise	Overall we enjoyed the hotel but there were a couple of quirks, some of which we knew about going in. When we checked in, it was a little earlier than their regular time and the room was ready. We were not asked which side of the hotel we wanted or if we had a floor preference (other guests were asked those questions when they checked in later). Possibly this was the only room available at the time so it is understandable. Our room was on the sixth floor overlooking Post St. The street noise on Friday and Saturday nights was very bad, but ear plugs helped. The room was very large and that was a big plus. Know what you are getting into if you sign up for the Timeshare sell. Keep your resolve if you just want the free gift. We also wondered about the spa facilities. Several people we ran into were not guest members and it seemed as if they just wanted a shower. Anyone could enter as you didn't need your key to open the facilities.	
