Nov 4 2008 	There must be two Donatellos in SF	We stayed at the Donatello hotel for 4 nights in October 2008. We chose it based on the the reviews in TripAdvisor. I am really amazed to re-read some of the comments that people have made, now that I have been at the hotel. What are they talking about? Is there another hotel Donatello in SF? This is a nice hotel? A nice lobby? There is hardly any lobby at the hotel and it is as simple as your can imagine. People who wrote that must have been sitting in the the lobby of the JW Marriott across the street and not the Donatello. As far as the beautiful rooms, maybe we just got unlucky and got a bad room but we checked other rooms from outside while the doors were opened for cleaning and they all looked basically the same. I have lived in SF for many years so I know the area and was not surprised by all the beggars and other bad and ugly elements that show up, mostly late at night, in that area. What I did not expect was to stay in such a disgusting room with paint peeling and mildew. The people at the reception are very nice but were totally ineffective. We arrived at the hotel two hours before the check-in time. Jesus, who somebody recommended for a review and a raise, and maybe he deserves it, welcomed us and checked us in. He took our mobile number and said that he will try to have us checked in as soon as possible and will call us when the room is ready. We never received the call and upon our return to the hotel we found out that the room was ready but that they forgot to call us - no big deal. What was a concern to us was the fact that the concierge could not find our luggage. It took him several minutes to realize that his colleague has left them in a conference room near the lobby - the door to that room was unlocked and anybody could have entered the room and take the luggage from there. With our hearts still pounding we took the elevator (dirty and in need of renovation) to the ninth floor. Our room was away from the street, which is highly recommended in this area, with a view of a car rental place and some other shady hotels and apartments in the same block - just next to the ice-maker and the door to the maintenance room - not such a big deal unless you want to sleep late in the morning. The worse part was the bathroom - SEE some pics attached. I called the &quot;effective&quot; and nice people at the reception and asked to speak to the manager. &quot;no problem - he will get back to you very soon&quot;. I called 3 times and left 3 messages and I never received a call back from the manager. I can go on with other examples of how ineffective the staff is  but nice  but all I can say is that I will never stay there again, not even for free.	
