Sep 28 2008 	Frisco Find	We stayed at the Donatelo September 24 through 26 and it was excellent! The location of the Hotel is perfect for seeing the sites of San Francisco with out the hassle. Location Location !!. The room was great with all ammenities required including a fridge and micro, flat screen TV mini stereo, Even some dishes! Bathroomwas fine though small compared to some hotels but who needs a huge bath, We liked the fact that windows were huge and opened although our view was not post card quality it didn't matter. We had a king bed and it was very comfortable. Breakfast was so so as there is limited choice juice coffee pasteries and bagels. There was fruit but not as fresh as it could have been. If I can complain about anything its serving food on paper plates and cups. For a hotel of this quality its sub standard, Now I know its picky but I equate eating off paper to dragging your nails across a blackboard! The staff was over the top in helping answer all questions and providing direction and personal favorities for site seeing. There is a night club/restaurant although we did not eat there ( there are numerous places around the hotel) we did go to the club and enjoy the entertainment. On another note when in Frisco do get the 3-day Muni pass do not get the 7-day pass. Do ride all three cable cars. Do not try to catch the the Masson or Hyde line at the bottom of Powel. Do go to Macy's and catch the &quot;F&quot; street car go all the way to Garibaldi Park and ride the Hydye line back or get off at Fishermans wharf and ride the Mason line. Ride the Californiia line in the afternoon so the sun is at your back for pictures looking back to the financial district. Do stay at the Donatello its the best bang for the buck with class.	
